  <sect2 role="package">
    <title/>

    <para>
      Toybox combines common Linux command line utilities together into a
      single executable. Its major design goals are simplicity, smallness and
      speed. It is an alternative to BusyBox which focuses on standards more
      than on compatibility with its GNU counterparts.
    </para>

    <segmentedlist>
      <segtitle>&buildtime;</segtitle>
      <segtitle>&diskspace;</segtitle>

      <seglistitem>
        <seg>&toybox-ch6-sbu;</seg>
        <seg>&toybox-ch6-du;</seg>
      </seglistitem>
    </segmentedlist>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of toybox</title>

    <para>First apply the following patch to allow building with the ash
    shell:</para>

<screen><userinput remap="pre">patch -p1 -i ../&toybox-ash-patch;</userinput></screen>

    <para>Instead of using the default DES method, use the more secure SHA-512
    method of password encryption:</para>

<screen><userinput remap="configure">sed '/TT.algo/ s/des/sha512/' -i toys/lsb/passwd.c</userinput></screen>

    <para>Ensure the toybox source is completely clean:</para>

<screen><userinput remap="pre">make distclean</userinput></screen>

    <para>Prepare toybox for compilation:</para>

<screen><userinput remap="configure">make defconfig</userinput></screen>

    <para>Compile the package:</para>

<screen><userinput remap="make">make</userinput></screen>

    <para>Install the package:</para>

<screen><userinput remap="install">install -v -m 755 toybox /bin &amp;&amp;
ln -sv toybox /bin/bzcat &amp;&amp;
ln -sfv toybox /bin/cat &amp;&amp;
